{{Unreferenced|date=May 2008}} '''Football (soccer) contracts''' are the legal contracts for both amateur and professional [[association football|football]]. Football contracts overlaps substantially with [[labor law]], [[contract law]] and [[tort law]]. Issues like [[defamation]], [[Privacy|privacy rights]] and [[intellectual property law]] are also an integral aspect of football contracts. This area been subject to a number of controversies since the 1990s (see the [[Bosman ruling]] and the [[Webster ruling]]). These cases have coincided with the rebalancing of player power and increased media scrutiny and commercialisation of football.
== See also == * [[George_Eastham#Newcastle_United|''Eastham v. Newcastle United'']], a similar 1963 court case in England. * [[Seitz decision]], a similar 1975 [[arbitration]] case in the [[United States of America|United States]]. * [[Bosman ruling]], established the limits of a sports contract in the EU * [[Kolpak ruling]], which extended Bosman to countries with an associate trading relationship with the EU, most notably the [[ACP countries]]
