{{Civil union}} '''Unregistered cohabitation''' is a legal status (sometimes ''de facto'') given to same-sex or opposite-sex couples in certain jurisdictions. They may be similar to [[common-law marriage|common-law marriages]].
More specifically, unregistered cohabitation may refer to: *{{flagicon|Australia}} [[Same-sex marriage in Australia#De facto relationships|Unregistered cohabitation in Australia]] and [[De facto relationship|De facto relationships in Australia]]<ref group=note name=note/> **{{flagicon|Australian Capital Territory}} Domestic relationships and domestic partnerships in the Australian Capital Territory<ref group=note name=note>Also recognizes another form of same-sex unions ([[Same-sex marriage|marriage]], [[civil unions]], [[domestic partnerships]]).</ref> **{{flagicon|New South Wales}} Domestic relationships in New South Wales<ref group=note name=note/> **{{flagicon|Northern Territory}} [[LGBT rights in the Northern Territory#De facto unions|''De facto'' unions in the Northern Territory]] **{{flagicon|Norfolk Island}} [[LGBT rights in Norfolk Island|''De facto'' unions in Norfolk Island]]<ref group=note name=note/> **{{flagicon|Queensland}} ''De facto'' relationships in Queensland<ref group=note name=note/> **{{flagicon|South Australia}} Close personal relationships in South Australia<ref group=note name=note/> **{{flagicon|Tasmania}} Personal relationships in Tasmania<ref group=note name=note/> **{{flagicon|Victoria}} Domestic relationships in Victoria<ref group=note name=note/> **{{flagicon|Western Australia}} [[LGBT rights in Western Australia#De facto unions|''De facto'' unions in Western Australia]] *{{flagicon|Canada}} Various ''de facto'' relationships in Canada<ref group=note name=note/> **{{flagicon|Alberta}} [[Adult interdependent relationship in Alberta]]<ref group=note name=note/> **{{flagicon|Manitoba}} [[Common-law relationships in Manitoba]]<ref group=note name=note/> **{{flagicon|Nova Scotia}} [[Domestic partnership in Nova Scotia]]<ref group=note name=note/> **{{flagicon|Quebec}} [[Civil unions in Quebec|Civil unions and ''de facto'' relationships in Quebec]] *{{flagicon|Colombia}} [[Recognition of same-sex unions in Colombia|''De facto'' unions in Colombia]] *{{flagicon|Croatia}} [[Recognition of same-sex unions in Croatia#Unregistered cohabitations|Unregistered cohabitation in Croatia]] *{{flagicon|Israel}} [[Unregistered cohabitation in Israel]]<ref group=note name=note/> *{{flagicon|Netherlands}} [[Samenlevingscontract|Samenlevingscontract in the Netherlands]]<ref group=note name=note/> *{{flagicon|New Zealand}} [[De facto relationship|''De facto'' relationships in New Zealand]]<ref group=note name=note/> *{{flagicon|Poland}} [[Recognition of same-sex unions in Poland|Unregistered cohabitation in Poland]] *{{flagicon|San Marino}} [[Recognition of same-sex unions in San Marino#Recognition of same-sex couples|Unregistered cohabitation in San Marino]]
Some other countries and sub-national regions recognize unregistered cohabitation, as listed in the ''[[Civil union]]'' article.
